Environment: local
 

### Run locally

  From the repository directory:

  npm install
  npm run dev

  Open:

  http://127.0.0.1:4321/

  To test the production build:

  npm run build
  npm run preview


  ---


  Then open the URL shown by Astro, normally:

  http://127.0.0.1:4321/

  You can also open dist/index.html directly after building. The current single-page shell supports this, though future nested pages will require the local server.

  ### GitHub Pages build

  Build using the repository subpath:

  PUBLIC_BASE_PATH=/sederot-course-catalog/ 
  npm run build

  The deployable output will be in:

  dist/

  GitHub Pages deployment automation is not configured yet. Selecting main directly in GitHub Pages will serve repository files—not the generated dist/ site.

  For proper GitHub Pages deployment, we need a GitHub Actions workflow that:

  1. Runs npm ci.
  2. Runs the Pages build command above.
  3. Uploads dist/.
  4. Deploys it to GitHub Pages.

  After deployment, the expected address is:

  https://idubi.github.io/sederot-course-catalog/

  This deployment workflow belongs to a later deployment task; I can add it now only if you want to expand TASK-003’s scope.



 
